Plugin Step: Load_virtual_image
Usage: 
User spicifies cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider, a property file for the image, providing the image name, version, reference id, url, etc.

This step will load a virtual image to IPAS/IWD. 

Plugin Step: Publish_deploy_vsp_cli

Usage: 
User spicifies cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider, environment profile name and also a directory cotaining pattern source in tar.gz format 
and property file that spycifies the parameters to deploy the pattern. And user could choose to publish the pattern only or to publish the pattern
and at the same time deploy a pattern to get an pattern instance. 

This step will publish a virtual system pattern and/or deploy the pattern to get an instance.

Plugin Step: Patterns Cleanup
Usage: 
User spicifies cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider, names for the patterns to be cleaned up and names for patterns that should be excluded.

This step will cleanup the virtual system patterns.

Plugin Step: Script Cleanup
Usage: 
User spicifies cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider, names for the scripts to be cleaned up and names for scripts that should be excluded.

This step will cleanup script packages in the catalog.

Plugin Step: Image Cleanup
Usage: 
User spicifies cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider, names for the images to be cleaned up and names for images that should be excluded.

This step will cleanup images in the catalog.



